Author: crypto-zoe#1154
Content: I have an issue with my Agama wallet. I sent two transactions to an address 3 days ago.  1st transaction was 825 KMD and the 2nd transaction was 25 KMD ... I should be getting 5% on 850 KMD which amounts to about 0.12 KMD per day.  HOWEVER!  I am only earning 0.003 KMD per day which is obviously not 5% on 850 coins, but it is 5% on 25 coins, meaning I am only getting rewarded for my most recent (smallest transaction) in my wallet.  Is this a know issue?  What is the solution?

Author: crypto-zoe#1154
Content: The atomic explorer shows my larger transaction "locktime field is not set" ?!

Author: Hermes#6934
Content: Currently this could have happened if you sent that transaction from a cold storage as ledger or an exchange because they are not using locktime on their internal wallets, what you can do in order to set the locktime is to send your balance to yourself by sending it to your own public address. After this procedure is done in Agama your locktime will be set

Content: @crypto-zoe
